    "comment": "Rationale: NOS-I antibody: Zymed (South San Francisco, CA) (Table 1). Is characterized in this paper (no shown).\n\n21/11/2017 Pim\nFig.3: Authors note: \"Although the limited resolution of light microscopy prevents definite conclusions, these data are consistent with the hypothesis that sGC concentrates in axon terminals, whereas NOS-I concentrates in postsynaptic densities.\"\nFig.6: \"Quantitative EM of randomly selected asymmetric synapses in the stratum radiatum confirmed that gold particles coding for NOS-I were predominantly postsynaptic, concentrating just cytoplasmic to the postsynaptic membrane, whereas particles coding for sGCβ were predominantly presynaptic, concentrating ~15-25 nm cytoplasmic to the presynaptic membrane (Fig. 6 C).\". Experimental description: Mixed species are used: \"All procedures related to the care and treatment of animals were in accordance with institutional and National Institutes of Health guidelines. Ten male Sprague Dawley rats (200-350 gm; Charles River, Raleigh, NC) and eight male mice..\"",
